description:
Madison College in Tennessee would for many years be a flagship self-supporting institution within the Seventh Day Adventist Church and would inspire many other schools and ministries globally. Later on, a network of self-supporting ministries would form what today is known as ASI - Adventist Laymens Services and Industries. They would prove to be a great blessing to the work of God, recognised all around the world.

To find out more about Madison College and ASI books visit our website to read our extended article.
